node.text: When you’re in Long Beach and in need of something sweet and delicious, look no further than @pietrisbakery and this HUUUUGE stack of Baklava pancakes with powdered sugar, syrup and Nutella. They have a loaded coffee bar so you’ll have options when it comes to what to pair with this epic stack! ☕️ Pietris Bakery is not a new establishment looking to gain fans either. Apparently they’re all over Greece, and consider themselves like “The Greek Porto’s” – their words. Can’t confirm that but can confirm that these pancakes were bomb.com! Definite must-get for brunch now that dine-in is reopening! Would you try these pancakes?! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love these pancakes! ✌️😎🥞 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

node.text: @birrieria.gmz is having their Grand Opening tomorrow in Hawthorne outside King Henry Pub, where in addition to slangin’ delicious, crispy birria pizzas like the one above – trust, it’s bomb – they’re going to have 4 FREE soft tacos to the first 30 ppl in line starting from 9AM until 4PM! 👊 But, if you’re more of a tacos dorados type of person, they’ll have those, too! Make sure to add @birrieria.gmz spicy chili oil, too! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love some FREE tacos tomorrow! ✌️😎🐄🌮🍕 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

node.text:
@berrybowl has been open for many years and it’s not a coincidence when you can serve healthy food at top quality in a creative way. Berry B. Does a great job and amid their selection of goodies your bound to create something that suits your fancy but if you feel overwhelmed they have a menu from smoothies to specialty bowls they can make for you right there! Like the Pitaya, Nutella, Tropical or Matcha bowls.🍵 You could even get a flight and sample multiple smaller size bowls. Berry bowl is delicious and when we say we could have this every morning to ease the stomach into the day, were not messin’ with you, it’s that tasty and refreshing. 👏 Berry Bowl is lucky to call coveted Highland Park home. Make sure to start you day here before you venture down York Blvd for the rest of the afternoon/evening. Like, comment or tag a friend who would love something healthy in the morning ! ✌️😎🥣🍇🍓🍌 #lafoodieguy #LAFG ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
If you’ve ever been to @thebuffalospot we can agree that it’s bomb unless you’re vegan or otherwise hate fried chicken. And hating fried chicken just doesn’t even make sense. This new sauce can be used on traditional bone-in wings, tenders, fries and with pretty much everything they offer. 👊 A tangy, lemony and Tajiny flavor dipped into the their savory-herby house sauce or ranch and you can call it a good Wing Wednesday right there! 😌 Our favorites are The Buff. Spot’s famous Buffalo Fries and, of course, the tenders bc they’re perfect for dipping. Like, comment or tag a friend you’d share this with! ✌️😎🍗 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
Have you ever heard of Tejuino before? Tejuino is a cold beverage made from fermented corn and popularly consumed in the Mexican state of Jalisco and Chihuahua. (Wiki) The drink is typically thick in consistency and we’ve seen it garnished in a variety of ways. This one was pretty darn good but tejuino is usually a too thick for our pallet. And though it would make it a different drink, our touch would be adding some club soda, gingerale or sprite to make it a little more crisper with the carbonation. And maybe some tequila if we wanna get loose. 🕺Our favorite part is that they set up outside @churrosdonabel right on Whittier Blvd., which, if you haven’t been to Whittier Blvd., is a whole vibe. Make sure you hit it up the little strip of trucks and vendors if you never have. 👍 Like, comment or tag a friend who would love this! ✌️😎🍹🌽#LAFoodieGuy #LAFG ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text: 🐙 @mariscoslabarquita at one point, don’t know if they still do, had tuna in a sweet and sour sauce that was similar to poke and it was worth the trip alone. They’re still popping with some of the freshest, tastiest mariscos in the valley and LA! THIS Tostada is like a seafood equivalent to a mayo-based chicken salad or tuna salad but with many types of fish. Give them a try if you’re in the area! Like, comment or tag a friend who loves seafood! ✌️😎🐠🦐 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG

Nutella-Covered Cheesecake, Lechera, Strawberries § Bananas || Dolce Cravings (@dolcecravingss) || Downey, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

The only other place in LA you can get this is at the LA County Fair; today is Sunday Funday and to certify it, why not get a gluttonous chocolate-covered cheesecake from @dolcecravingss in Downey. They’re located next to/inside Emporio Sushi and Mariscos so after your meal, grab some dessert! 🎂 Would you try this?! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love this tonight! ✌️😎🍰 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #downey

node.text:
Al Pastor Angel’s Potato || Angel’s Tijuana Tacos (@angelstijuanatacos) || North Hollywood, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

If you like tacos and live in LA, you’ve probably been to @angelstijuanatacos at least once or twice. The tacos, vampiros, burritos are all amazing but this potato is definitely something deliciously different and big enough to feed the whole fam. You can’t go wrong if you’re a fan of baked potatoes and tacos – this item is like the two fused together. Good thing for us is that Angel’s is usually open in 5-7 locations every night except Mondays. Just check their IG to see where they’re posted daily. 😆 We’ll then, gonna have to get some tacos now after seeing this. Like, comment or tag a friend who would love this tonight! ✌️😎🌮#LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #northhollywood

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

@mariscoselpatron818 has been holding it down in Pacoima for years now and has built up quite the following , so much so that they’re opening up a second truck next to their birria truck at 649 W Arrow Highway TOMORROW IN THE AM!! 🛻 Some of the go-tos are the cheesy shrimp tacos dorados, the Pastelaso (seafood tower) and shrimp or fish ceviches! 🦐 Do you like seafood?! node.text:
Texas Toast, American Cheese, Hot Chicken Tenders, Coleslaw, Pickles § Special Sauce Sanwich || Richie’s Hot Chicken (@richies_hotchicken) || West Covina, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

Texas toast is good enough by itself but use it as the vehicle to drive some fried hot chicken into your mouth? Take my moneys. 💵 @richies_hotchicken also offer buns and tender plates, too! Stop by the spot if you’re east of the city but got that hankering for hot chicken!! Would you try this?! Like, comment or tag a friend who loves fried chicken tenders! ✌️😎🐓🍞 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #westcovina

node.text:
Cheesy Asada Mulita, Onion, Cilantro, Salsa § Guacamole || Taqueria El Poblano (@taqueria_el_poblano) || Compton, CA

Video Credit 🎥: @lafoodieguy 

Tacos are amazing, we all know this, and there’s something about a tortilla stuffed with your favorite savory meats that make them a go-to Friday night meal. 🔥 @taqueria_el_poblano has been making Compton some of the best TJ style tacos for years now from basically a stand! They got so busy that they were able to open up their NEW brick and mortar in the same town! The result of hard work, passion and dedication! 🙌 Handmade tortillas, flame-grilled meats, salsas made the old-fashioned way in the molcajete and everything else you’d want from a taco spot! Have you been to El Poblano?! Like, comment or tag a friend who would love this spot! ✌️😎🌮 #LAFoodieGuy #LAFG #compton ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
